            "sample": [
              "\"robustness\": \"standard\",",
              "  \"signals\": {",
              "    \"iteration\": 2,",
              "    \"idea\": \"Refactor the video editor to be elegant, well-structured, and aligned with the reigh-app architecture at /Users/peteromalley/Documents/reigh-workspace/reigh-app.\\n\\nCURRENT STATE OF VIDEO EDITOR:\\n- App.tsx is 1325 lines (god component handling everything)\\n- App.css is 1224 lines (one giant file, no scoping)\\n- State management is useState/useRef chains in App.tsx\\n- No tests, dead code (DebugTrack, DEBUG_MODE, LivePreview.tsx)\\n- ~3745 lines in viewer/src, ~1435 lines in shared/\\n\\nREIGH-APP ARCHITECTURE TO ALIGN WITH:\\n- Vite + React 18 + TypeScript (same stack)\\n- Tailwind CSS + shadcn-ui components (NOT plain CSS)\\n- React Query for server state, Context for global UI state\\n- Feature-based directory structure: tools/[feature]/pages|components|hooks|settings\\n- Path aliases (@/* -> src/*)\\n- No CSS files - pure Tailwind utility classes\\n- Supabase for backend (auth, db, storage, realtime)\\n- Existing video components: StyledVideoPlayer, VideoPortionTimeline, VideoPortionEditor\\n- Task system for async operations (like rendering)\\n- Settings persistence via useAutoSaveSettings\\n- @dnd-kit for drag-and-drop\\n- Konva for canvas rendering\\n- lucide-react for icons\\n\\nREFACTORING GOALS:\\n\\n1. BREAK UP App.tsx into focused modules:\\n   - TimelineState context/hook (clip selection, track management, save/load)\\n   - TimelineEditor component (the timeline UI)\\n   - PreviewPanel component (Remotion player + overlay editor)\\n   - PropertiesPanel component (ClipPanel + TrackPanel in sidebar)\\n   - Toolbar component (add track, add text, render, zoom controls)\\n\\n2. REPLACE App.css with Tailwind:\\n   - Convert all CSS to Tailwind utility classes\\n   - Use shadcn-ui components where applicable (Button, Select, Slider, Popover, Card, etc.)\\n   - Remove the CSS file entirely\\n\\n3. STATE MANAGEMENT aligned with reigh-app:\\n   - TimelineContext for editor state (selected clip, selected track, current time)\\n   - React Query for loading/saving timeline.json (with proper query keys)\\n   - useAutoSaveSettings pattern for editor preferences (zoom level, collapsed sections)\\n\\n4. DIRECTORY STRUCTURE matching reigh-app's tool pattern:\\n   tools/video-editor/\\n     pages/VideoEditorPage.tsx\\n     components/\\n       TimelineEditor/\\n       PreviewPanel/\\n       PropertiesPanel/\\n       Toolbar/\\n       TrackLabel/\\n       ClipAction/\\n     hooks/\\n       useTimelineState.ts\\n       useTimelineSync.ts\\n       useCrossTrackDrag.ts\\n       useOverlayEditor.ts\\n     contexts/\\n       TimelineContext.tsx\\n     lib/\\n       timeline-data.ts\\n       coordinate-utils.ts\\n\\n5. CLEAN UP:\\n   - Remove dead code (DebugTrack, DEBUG_MODE, LivePreview.tsx)\\n   - Remove viewer/.gitignore (use root .gitignore)\\n   - Clean up unused imports and files\\n   - Add proper TypeScript strict typing throughout\\n\\n6. COMPONENT LIBRARY alignment:\\n   - Use shadcn Button, Select, Slider, Popover, Card, Input components\\n   - Use lucide-react icons instead of emoji (play/pause/skip buttons)\\n   - Use @dnd-kit for drag-and-drop instead of custom pointer event handlers\\n   - Use Tailwind for all styling\\n\\nCONSTRAINTS:\\n- Keep the shared/ compositions layer intact (it works well)\\n- Keep timeline.json schema unchanged\\n- Keep the Remotion Player integration\\n- Keep all current functionality working\\n- This is a refactor, not a feature change\","
            ]
          },
          {
