            "sample": [
              "\"robustness\": \"standard\",",
              "  \"signals\": {",
              "    \"iteration\": 2,",
              "    \"idea\": \"Fix clip positioning, override system, and organize the ClipPanel UI.\\n\\nTHREE CONNECTED ISSUES:\\n\\n1. CANVAS POSITIONING ALIGNMENT: The drag/resize box on the preview is misaligned with the actual clip rendering - it shows offset to the top-left. The coordinate projection between the overlay div and the Remotion Player content needs to be fixed. The box must exactly match where the clip visually appears.\\n\\n2. CLIP-LEVEL OVERRIDES: When a user manually positions/resizes a clip on the canvas (or edits x/y/width/height in the panel), that should OVERRIDE the track-level scale/fit settings for that specific clip. Currently track-level scale still applies even when a clip has explicit positioning. Need: (a) clip-level x/y/width/height takes full precedence over track fit/scale, (b) a 'Reset to track defaults' button on each clip that clears the override and returns to inheriting from the track, (c) visual indicator in the ClipPanel showing which values are overridden vs inherited.\\n\\n3. CLIPANEL ORGANIZATION: The right sidebar ClipPanel is poorly organized - all settings are jumbled together. Reorganize into clear sections:\\n   - HEADER: clip ID, asset name, track, close button\\n   - TIMING: at, from, to, speed (the when/duration controls)\\n   - POSITION & SIZE: x, y, width, height with a 'Reset to track defaults' button (only shown when clip has overrides)\\n   - EFFECTS: entrance dropdown + duration, exit dropdown + duration, continuous dropdown + intensity  \\n   - AUDIO: volume slider, mute button (only for clips with audio)\\n   - TRANSITIONS: type dropdown + duration (only when clip has predecessor)\\n   - TEXT: content, font, size, color (only for text clips)\\n   Each section should be a collapsible card with a header. Empty/irrelevant sections should be hidden.\\n\\nThe canvas positioning, the override system, and the panel organization all need to work together - editing position in the panel should match what you see on the canvas, and both should correctly override track defaults.\\n\\nCONSTRAINTS: All changes persist to timeline.json. The Remotion renderer (VisualClip.tsx) must respect clip overrides. Canvas overlay must account for letterboxing, PREVIEW_SCALE, and track-level scale when computing the visual box position.\","
            ]
          },
