              "\"robustness\": \"standard\",",
              "  \"signals\": {",
              "    \"iteration\": 2,",
              "    \"idea\": \"Integrate Remotion rendering into the EXISTING viewer/editor (viewer/ directory). The viewer already has: drag-drop timeline (@xzdarcy/react-timeline-editor), overlay positioning (OverlayEditor.tsx), asset panel (AssetPanel.tsx), live preview (LivePreview.tsx), and auto-save to timeline config. The new Remotion executor also built editing features as a portal overlay on Studio (EditorOverlay.tsx, ClipPanel.tsx, editor-utils.ts, save-config.ts) - these features should be merged INTO the existing viewer, not exist as a separate editor. Specifically: 1) Replace the viewer's canvas-based LivePreview.tsx with @remotion/player showing the actual Remotion composition for pixel-perfect preview. 2) Port the useful new features (split clip, mute, property editing via ClipPanel, save serialization from save-config.ts) into the existing viewer UI. 3) Update the viewer to read/write timeline.json + asset-registry.json instead of timeline.yaml. 4) Remove the EditorOverlay portal from Remotion Studio (it shouldn't have its own editor UI). 5) Keep Remotion Studio as a standalone preview-only tool. The result: ONE editor (the viewer), powered by Remotion for preview and rendering.\","
            ]
