            "sample": [
              "\"robustness\": \"standard\",",
              "  \"signals\": {",
              "    \"iteration\": 2,",
              "    \"idea\": \"Add basic visual editing features to the Remotion Studio timeline. The project already has a working Remotion composition that reads timeline.json and renders video/audio/overlay tracks. Now we need to add interactive editing directly in the browser UI. Five features: (1) DRAG clips to reposition them on the timeline (change clip.at), (2) SPEED control - zoom/speed up/slow down clips (change clip.speed), (3) CROP/TRIM the ends of clips (change clip.from and clip.to), (4) SPLIT clips at the playhead into two separate clips, (5) MUTE clips (toggle clip.volume to 0 or back). All edits must write back to timeline.json so they persist and are picked up by Python tools. The existing viewer/ has a working drag-drop timeline using @xzdarcy/react-timeline-editor that can inform the approach. The current Remotion project is at remotion/ with compositions in remotion/src/timeline/. KEY CONSTRAINTS: (1) Edits write to timeline.json - the shared config that Python tools also read/write. (2) The UI runs inside or alongside Remotion Studio (npx remotion studio). (3) Keep it simple - these are basic NLE controls, not a full editor rebuild. (4) Project is open source.\","
            ]
          },
